The paper deals with handling inconsistency in knowledge bases, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and databases (cs.DB). The use of recursive algorithms and the analysis of execution time suggest that the paper may also fall under the category of algorithms and complexity (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the mention of managing inconsistencies may also suggest the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
